Title: Quantum Integrability of Certain Boundary Conditions
Authors: M. Moriconi (ICTP, Trieste), A. De Martino (SISSA and INFN, Trieste)
Comments: 11 pages, Latex file, minor changes, one reference added
Report-no: ICTP/IR/98/19, SISSA/EP/98/101
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B447 (1999) 292-297
\\
  We study the quantum integrability of the O(N) nonlinear $\sigma$ (nls) model
and the O(N) Gross-Neveu (GN) model on the half-line. We show that the \nls
model is integrable with Neumann, Dirichlet and a mixed boundary condition, and
that the GN model is integrable if $\psi_+^a\x=\pm\psi_-^a\x$. We also comment
on the boundary condition found by Corrigan and Sheng for the O(3) nls model.
